                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <head>No. 585.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName
                            type="to">Sickles</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 7, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The capture on the high seas of a vessel bearing the American flag presents a
                    very grave question, which will need investigation, and the summary proceedings
                    resulting in the punishment of death, with such rapid haste, will attract
                    attention as inhuman and in violation of the civilization of the age. And if it
                    prove that an American citizen has been wrongfully executed, this Government
                    will require most ample reparation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH,</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
